<TEXT>
nelson mandela wrapped up his first visit 
to the united states by promising to return in october for a look 
at the problems of american indians 
two american indians said they delivered a onepage invitation 
and gifts to a mandela representative as the south african black 
nationalist leader arrived at oakland international airport for a 
rally saturday 
the letter outlined several problems and said it has been 500 
years since the first nonindians came to this land and began the 
destruction of our culture said one of the women betty cooper 
who is the director of the native american alcoholism program in 
oakland 
mandela told 58000 people at oakland coliseum that he was 
disturbed by what he read he said he will visit the indian 
areas of the country for a look at the struggle of american 
indians 
the rally speech was one of the first occasions mandela spoke 
about the plight of ethnic groups in the united states 
chief among the concerns american indian leaders would like to 
tell mandela about are poverty unemployment and the lack of health 
care plaguing indians on reservations and in cities cooper said 
we told him in the letter that we share many of the same 
problems of his country and would like to have the opportunity to 
share them with him she said 
mandela 71 said he would have looked into the problems before 
he completed his eightcity tour in the united states but 
unfortunately my schedule is very tight but i can assure the 
leaders of the american indian community that i will return in 
october 
cooper and sally gallegos executive director of the 
oaklandbased consortium of united indian nations said they 
approached mandela at the airport but were kept away they handed 
the letter and gifts to a mandela representative instead 
the gifts included a sacred blanket and a shawl for mandelas 
wife winnie and some indian medicine 
roger wilkins national coordinator of the mandela tour said 
mandela already had planned a return visit before he received the 
invitation 
the letters from the native americans were not the proximate 
cause of his decision to come back but since he was coming back 
he would look into the issue wilkins said 
mandela and his wife left oakland on saturday for ireland via 
canada earlier saturday he took a stroll through downtown los 
angeles streets he stopped several times to shake hands with 
admirers including a homeless man in a wheelchair 
mandela is touring 14 countries on a roundtheworld trip to 
raise money for the struggle against apartheid south africas 
system of racial segregation 
