<TEXT>
jubilant east germans set off fireworks 
drank toasts and flung the currency of their old communist state 
into the air sunday as the two germanys united their economies 
banks were open for special sunday hours and thousands of east 
germans lined up to get their new currency west german marks 
stores in west berlin and in border villages in west germany were 
bracing for a crush of shoppers on monday morning 
the new treaty merges the two nations into a single economic 
entity and sets east germany on the path to a freemarket economy 
also all remaining border controls between the two nations were 
officially eliminated 
for many germans both east and west sunday ranked in 
significance with the fall of the communist government in october 
last year and the opening of the berlin wall a month later 
the economic unification marks the effective end of east german 
sovereignty and the most important step toward a single germany 
the german states now will work on a political treaty that will 
likely result in common elections and the creation of a single 
nation in december 
one of the thousands of east germans who lined up to collect the 
new currency was hansjoachim corsalle 41 who delivers coal for a 
living he withdrew the equivalent of 1200 in west german marks 
from his account to take his family on vacation 
im used to standing in line he said yesterday for 
instance i waited in line for five hours to get enough gas for the 
vacation 
alexandra meier 19 saw the day as the beginning of prosperity 
i hope that well never have to stand in line again she 
said hopefully well be able to buy whatever we want 
east german stores were closed during the weekend as workers 
remodeled the former stateowned shops and stocked them with 
truckloads of western products that stand to dominate the newly 
opened consumer market 
east germany is expected to face widespread joblessness as its 
newly independent factories and businesses are forced to compete 
with the west 
prime minister lothar de maiziere urged optimism and criticized 
those who dwell on predictions of massive unemployment 
there will be problems and hardships but from now on things 
will improve for us he said in remarks prepared for an address 
to the nation on sunday 
thanks to west germany we have opportunities no other east 
european country has he said lets take advantage of them 
in an interview with the west german newspaper bild am sonntag 
de maiziere said prosperity will come to east germany within five 
years 
it will happen because it must happen he said now is the 
time to roll up our sleeves and work hard and we will do that 
</TEXT>
