it was the night before the end of the jvc jazz 
festival and there was a lot of serious listening going on 
with good reason 
saxophonist stan getz delivered the goods friday night at 
carnegie hall he played most of the time he was on stage he 
explored a range of composers and a range of emotions he played 
with horn miked and on several selections unamplified 
he played blues and ballads rollicking tune latininflected 
ones too 
he led subtly but authoritatively a superb quartet on some 
numbers two synthesizers were added blending easily into the 
groups sound 
getz who has fought cancer for a few years is at the top of 
his form only a handful of saxophonists can play as well or more 
expressively 
the pianist kenny barron whom getz called the other half of 
my heart also played forcefully and delicately their closing 
duet a benny carter tune written for the nations bicentennial 
celebration topped the evening 
also backing getz up were bassist alex blake who caressed and 
thumped his instrument in rousing fashion and drummer terri lynne 
carrington who played well throughout the night she took few 
solos but her deft playing supported the group playing 
synthesizers were eddie del barrio and frank zottoli 
the group played selections from a recent album 
anniversary as well as from a new one passionato in 
addition getz played music composed by among others thad jones 
