<TEXT>
the 28th communist party congress beginning monday 
is the most powerful party forum and is to vote on new rules on the 
partys structure and operations here are excerpts based on a text 
of the proposed rules published thursday in the party daily pravda 
the congress of the cpsu communist party of the soviet union 
elects the party chairman and his deputy 
the congress elects the central committee 
for decisions of political and organizational questions during 
the period between congresses the central committee elects from 
among its members a presidium of the party central committee 
a plenum of the central committee elects from the leaders of 
commissions a secretariat of the central committee headed by a 
first secretary of the central committee 
elections to party posts are to be conducted by secret ballot 
with no limit on the number of candidates to win a candidate must 
receive a majority 
party officials can hold office for no more than two 
consecutive terms the rules dont give the length of terms 
freedom of expression of opinions juxtaposition of various 
views and platforms open criticism and selfcriticism are fostered 
in the party but the proposed rules also place limits the 
creation of fractions in the cpsu with their own internal 
organization and discipline is not allowed which does not limit 
the right of communists to join together according to platforms in 
the course of debate 
a party member it says is free to participate in the work 
of social organizations and movements whose activity is built on 
the basis of the ussr constitution and does not contradict 
socialist ideas 
communist parties of the union republics are independent on 
the basis of the program and statutes of the cpsu they work out 
their own program and normative documents 
the rules retain party cells in the armed forces the kgb and 
interior troops 
in a more clear separation of powers they say party 
organizations and committees dont allow a mixture of functions 
with government and management organs carry out a political line 
of the party through communists working in them 
abandoning the partys claim to a monopoly on politics the 
rules say the cpsu like other socialpolitical organizations 
is fighting for political leadership in society at free elections 
to the soviets of peoples deputies and through other forms 
