germany set off on a bold adventure sunday by 
forging a single economy and scrapping internal borders and 
leaders in east and west said difficulties lie ahead 
east germans cheered honked horns and set off fireworks to 
welcome their new west german money which put fancy cars and 
vacations to brazil within reach many suddenly had thousands of 
dollars worth of the longcoveted currency 
at border crossings that once were impenetrable smiling 
families walked drove and bicycled back and forth without a 
policeman in sight 
more than 200 people were killed as they tried to escape over 
the same borders during communist rule erich honecker the 
hardline former leader who was toppled last october is now the 
target of a murder probe into the killings 
in berlin sunday officials reopened eight subway ghost 
stations that hads been shut down by construction of the berlin 
wall in 1961 another major step toward unifying the city 
still there was sobering talk from officials sunday especially 
in light of the possibility that east german businesses will start 
filing for bankruptcy as early as monday strikes are also expected 
as the pressure from western business builds 
one east german company the elektrowerk electronicon of gera 
announced onequarter of its 5000 workers would work reduced 
shifts beginning monday 
there have been predictions that up to 4 million east germans 
could be put out of work as the country struggles to rebuild an 
economy ravaged by decades of communist mismanagement and 
inefficiency 
a majority of the houses were built before the turn of the 
century shortages of materials have left towns in sad disrepair 
and basics like roads and telecommunications are falling apart 
it will take hard work until we have reached unity and 
freedom prosperity and social balance for all germans west 
