<TEXT>
west germany was the worlds biggest exporter 
for the first three months of 1990 regaining its leadership over 
the united states the international monetary fund reported sunday 
west germany increased its exports to 998 billion up more 
than 18 percent over the first quarter of last year the us 
increase of nearly 10 percent brought its total to 972 billion 
in 1989 the united states regained first place with 364 
billion worth of exports compared to west germanys 341 billion 
west germany first forged ahead in 1986 
experts say the economic unification of west germany and east 
germany which officially began sunday could put the united 
germany ahead of the us as the worlds biggest exporter for years 
to come the fund gave no figures for east germany which is not 
among its 151 member countries 
japan trailed in a distant third place with 274 billion worth 
of exports for 1989 and 68 billion for the first quarter of this 
year 
the united states remained by far the worlds biggest importer 
with 125 billion in foreignmade goods coming into the country in 
the first quarter of the year that compared with 118 billion a 
year earlier west germanys imports also increased to 78 billion 
from 65 billion 
west germany had a 22 billion surplus of exports over imports 
for the quarter compared with a us deficit of 28 billion 
japan striving to reduce complaints about its big export surplus 
was the only one of the seven major industrial countries to report 
a drop in exports for the quarter it still had a 12 billion 
surplus for the period second only to west germanys 
the 22 countries that the fund classifies as industrial had a 
total deficit of 32 billion in trade with the rest of the world 
for the first quarter of 1990 that was up from 24 billion in the 
first quarter of 1989 
adding up annual surpluses and deficits for the first time the 
fund reported that the industrial countries had an aggregate trade 
deficit with the rest of the world in 1989 of 110 billion up from 
80 billion in 1988 
italy along with west germany reported the most rapid gains in 
both imports and exports for the quarter but because of changes in 
exchange rates italy increased its deficit to 73 billion for the 
quarter compared with 71 billion in the first quarter of 1989 
</TEXT>
