<TEXT>
lithuanias sole oil refinery was back in 
operation sunday after the kremlin eased its embargo on the baltic 
republic 
lidia cheblakova a duty officer said the mazhiekiai refinery 
in northwestern lithuania was receiving 25000 tons of oil a day 
compared to the normal preembargo level of 45000 
soviet officials resumed pumping oil to lithuania on saturday 
starting to fulfill its promise to lift the 10week blockade in 
return for a moratorium on the republics declaration of 
independence 
the soviet government cut off shipments of all oil most natural 
gas and numerous other items to lithuania on april 18 in attempt to 
force it to rescind its march 11 declaration of independence 
the lithuanian parliament accepted a compromise friday that 
traded a 100day moratorium on the declaration for an immediate end 
to the blockade and the start of negotiations 
the subject of lithuanias came up in pope john paul iis 
prayers in rome on sunday while he didnt comment on the dispute 
over independence the pontiff prayed that conditions would improve 
for lithuanian catholics and that there would be a victory of the 
cross in the soviet republic 
ms cheblakova said in a telephone interview the full supply of 
oil will be resumed as soon as the refinery is ready to receive it 
just one of mazhiekiais two plants was operating because there 
are not enough workers available many were released on vacation or 
laid off when the blockade started she said 
officials said refined oil from the mazhiekiai plant the only 
one in lithuania would not reach consumers for at least two weeks 
for technical reasons it refines about 12 million tons of 
petroleum products a year a quarter of it used in lithuania 
the refinery employs 2000 people who were thrown out of work 
by the cutoff the plant processed its last oil april 23 as the 
blockade exhausted reserves that came from the single pipeline 
feeding the plant from the russian city of polotsk 
the huge plant provided much of the gasoline and industrial fuel 
for lithuania latvia estonia the russian city of kaliningrad and 
parts of byelorussia before it shut down for lack of oil 
lithuania and its 38 million people are entirely dependent upon 
the soviet union for its oil and gas which it receives at highly 
subsidized prices 
lithuania and its baltic neighbors latvia and estonia were 
independent from moscow between the two world wars but were 
forcibly absorbed back into the soviet union by josef stalin in 
1940 
all three are seeking to regain their independence although 
estonia and latvia have taken a slower approach to separation from 
the soviet union than lithuania 
in his homily the pope noted that lithuanian bishops recently 
celebrated a special mass in which they implored the crucified 
christ to shorten the days of difficult testing to which lithuanian 
believers continue to be subjected 
may the lord give them this grace assuring the victory of the 
cross the polishborn pope said 
the pontiff speaking at a mass at the lithuanian college of san 
casimiro in rome said the cross has become the special symbol of 
the lithuanians of the people of the families of the communities 
and all the society 
soviet authorities in the past have refused john paul permission 
to travel to lithuania which is overwhelmingly catholic 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

