vincent a buddy cianci jr 
convicted felon media personality former mayor is trying to 
become mayor again 
and if the 49yearold independent candidate wins in november 
it will be a journey cianci says will make him a better leader 
a lot of people say they didnt like me as mayor but they 
liked me on the radio cianci said the radio station made me 
listen and made me aware that there were other points of view 
its kept me sharp and its kept me current 
elected in 1974 he was forced out of office 10 years later 
after he attacked his estranged wifes lover with a fireplace log 
an ashtray and a lit cigarette he pleaded no contest to two 
assault charges and in april 1984 he received a fiveyear 
suspended sentence and probation 
after his ouster cianci wanted to run in the special mayoral 
election and complete his fouryear term in the states largest 
city with 160000 residents but the state supreme court ruled that 
