<TEXT>
china on sunday launched its largest census ever 
mobilizing 7 million people to count the worlds most populous 
nation 
for the next 10 days census takers throughout the country 
from the crowded coastal cities to its desolate western regions 
will be knocking on doors to get the latest count of chinas 
estimated 11 billion people 
censustakers arrived at 9 am at zhongnanhai the redwalled 
compound housing communist party headquarters and homes of the top 
leaders the evening tv news reported 
the report showed two young census workers interviewing 
communist party general secretary jiang zemin and premier li peng 
running through the standard questions of name age and address 
even though in their cases the answers are common knowledge 
census workers also arrived early at the homes of ordinary 
citizens 
they didnt stay very long just asked their questions and 
left said a 50yearold worker from central beijing who gave 
only her surname kang this was actually their last visit not 
their first theyve come several times already getting ready for 
the census 
since spring officials have been making checks to confirm that 
household registrations are up to date census workers have also 
staged practice runs visiting families and filling out 
questionnaires 
to ensure the accuracy of the head count china is sending its 
census takers doortodoor for the first time previously 
residents were asked to visit census stations for the three 
censuses conducted since the communists came to power in 1949 
publicity for the census has been ubiquitous since the spring 
billboards and banners remind citizens that a successful census 
requires their cooperation and newspaper editorials explain why 
its necessary to count the nations people 
for the past two months government notices posted on a low 
green fence in kangs neighborhood have kept residents informed of 
the census proceedings 
its a very necessary task said another resident who did 
not give his name its just like a family how can you take 
care of your family if you dont even know how many of you there 
are and what everyones doing 
kang and others noted that the 21item questionnaire was more 
detailed than that of the previous census in 1982 
most however said they didnt mind answering questions about 
each family members name age education level and occupation as 
well as about household features and childbearing conditions for 
women 
but the same questions strike fear in the hearts of china 20 
millionstrong floating population who have moved to cities 
without permission and among those who have had children in 
violation of chinas strict family planning policy 
in beijing census workers headed out saturday evening to count 
the floating population many of whom work during the day and 
return home late said zhu yilin head of the municipal census 
office 
initial results of the census will be published in october but 
it will take nearly two years to process the data they collect 
